<item>
            <title>[DERBY-6318] Simplify setting of possibly null parameters in XPLAIN descriptors</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-6318</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I noticed that the various XPLAIN descriptor classes need to set lots of numeric parameters on a PreparedStatement, using the following idiom to allow null values:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        if (parse_time != null)&lt;br/&gt;
            ps.setLong(2, parse_time.longValue());&lt;br/&gt;
        else&lt;br/&gt;
            ps.setNull(2, Types.BIGINT);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The same thing could have been achieved by using a single call to setObject(), like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        ps.setObject(2, parse_time, Types.BIGINT);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This would make the methods shorter and clearer.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
